---
description: Security and operational rules
alwaysApply: true
---

Security rules:

- Never log secrets, tokens, or full auth payloads.
- Do not trust client input. Validate and narrow types at boundaries.
- Prefer server-side authorization checks for sensitive actions.
- Return safe errors to clients. Keep internal details out of user-facing responses.
- Use environment variables for runtime configuration.
- Minimize third-party dependencies.
- For auth, payments, webhooks, or admin actions, be conservative and explicit.
